					<h3>Yes we have been seeing whales, whale, whales!</h3>
					<p>Yes we have been seeing whales, whale, whales!</p>
					<p>Last Wed 5/6 we saw 2 pairs of mother &amp; calf gray whales.  We also saw many sea lions and a sea otter mom &amp; baby.</p>
					<p>Fri 5/8 we were on an inner bay cruise close to shore and saw a humpback whale,</p>
					<p>Sat 5/9 we saw about 20 Orcas!!! They were coming up to the boat and passing underneath. They also were riding the wake and bow riding. There were also a few humpback trying to get in on the fun.</p>
					<p>Sunday May 10th we saw Humpback just a few miles out. They did multiple breaches and behaviors.</p>
					<p>Sea Lions on every trip and Sea birds, Albatross! We also have heard from many people seeing Gray Whales and Humpbacks from West Cliff &amp; SeaCliff Beach/Cement Ship. Our next trips are Wed 5/13, Fri 5/15, Sat 5/16 &amp; Sun 5/17.</p>
